{"findings":[{"id":"F-001","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"First-time same-chain borrow bypasses collateral check","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:152","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:157","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:161","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:167"],"claim":"`CoreRouter.borrow` computes `borrowAmount` as `0` when `currentBorrow.borrowIndex == 0`, then checks `collateral >= borrowAmount`. For first-time borrowers this always passes, yet the function still executes a real borrow and transfers underlying.","impact":"Any account can open an initial borrow without sufficient collateral, creating immediate bad debt and enabling pool drain up to available liquidity.","paths":["CoreRouter.borrow -> getBorrowBalance.borrowIndex == 0 -> borrowAmount = 0 -> collateral check trivially passes -> LErc20.borrow(_amount) -> underlying transferred to borrower"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-002","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"Cross-chain borrow trusts stale source collateral snapshot (TOCTOU)","locations":["LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:138","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:143","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:617","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:622"],"claim":"`borrowCrossChain` sends a one-time collateral snapshot (`payload.collateral`) from source chain, and destination execution validates only against this stale value instead of current source-chain collateral at execution time.","impact":"A borrower can initiate a cross-chain borrow, then reduce/remove collateral on the source chain before message execution, resulting in undercollateralized remote debt and protocol insolvency risk.","paths":["Chain A: borrowCrossChain captures collateral and sends message","Before destination execution: borrower redeems/withdraws source collateral","Chain B: _handleBorrowCrossChainRequest checks stale payload.collateral and executes borrow"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-003","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"Cross-chain debt is excluded from accounting due impossible EID condition","locations":["LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:495","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:497","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:499","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:617","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:227"],"claim":"`LendStorage.borrowWithInterest` only counts `crossChainCollaterals` entries when both `destEid == currentEid` and `srcEid == currentEid`. Real cross-chain entries on destination chain have `srcEid != currentEid`, so they are skipped.","impact":"Borrow checks underestimate existing cross-chain debt (enabling repeated over-borrow), and cross-chain liquidation max-repay can collapse to zero, effectively preventing liquidation.","paths":["_handleBorrowCrossChainRequest -> getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral -> borrowWithInterest excludes existing cross-chain collateral debt -> new borrow allowed against understated debt","liquidateCrossChain -> getMaxLiquidationRepayAmount(false) -> borrowWithInterest returns 0 -> repayAmount check fails for real liquidations"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-004","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Source-chain cross-chain debt update drops accrued interest when refreshing borrow index","locations":["LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:710","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:711","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:712"],"claim":"When an existing cross-chain borrow is updated in `_handleValidBorrowRequest`, principal is set to `oldPrinciple + payload.amount` and borrowIndex is overwritten with a newer index, without first normalizing old principal to the new index.","impact":"Repeated borrows can under-account true debt versus accrued debt, weakening solvency checks and reducing liquidation effectiveness.","paths":["Existing crossChainBorrows record at old borrowIndex","New ValidBorrowRequest arrives with higher payload.borrowIndex","Contract writes principle += amount and borrowIndex = payload.borrowIndex without accruing old principal"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-005","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Public cross-chain operations are protocol-fee sponsored, enabling native fee griefing","locations":["LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:113","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:156","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:172","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:794","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:820"],"claim":"User-callable cross-chain functions trigger `_send`, which uses contract-native funds for LayerZero messaging (`_payNative` uses router balance and `_lzSend` is funded from contract balance) instead of caller-paid fees.","impact":"Attackers can spam cross-chain calls to burn router native balance and deny service for legitimate cross-chain operations until re-funded.","paths":["Attacker repeatedly calls borrowCrossChain / repayCrossChainBorrow / liquidateCrossChain","Each call sends LayerZero message funded by router-native balance","Router native reserve is depleted and later messages fail"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-006","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Cross-chain liquidation finalization uses inconsistent token identity and impossible lookup parameters","locations":["LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:355","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:361","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:445","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:448","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:452","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:479"],"claim":"`LiquidationSuccess/Failure` messages reuse `payload.destlToken` from the collateral chain, but receiving handlers treat it as a local token (`lTokenToUnderlying(payload.destlToken)`), and success lookup also hardcodes `destEid` to `0`. This causes mismatched lookups/reverts.","impact":"Cross-chain liquidation completion can fail deterministically, leaving cross-chain liquidation flow broken and creating unresolved debt/collateral state transitions or stuck message retries.","paths":["_handleLiquidationExecute